eeper than our\nIRSF images. A modified version of our photometry pipeline was used to derive\nthe photometric parameters of these UKIDSS galaxies. Good agreement was found\nbetween the respective $K_s$-band isophotal magnitudes. These comparisons\nconfirm the robustness of the isophotal parameters and demonstrate that the\nIRSF images do not suffer from foreground contamination, after star removal,\nnor under-estimate the isophotal fluxes of ZoA galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2016 19:50:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-07"}
