ination promotion efforts. Additionally, it can be\napplied to future surveys, only requiring 3.6% of the variables in the CCHS for\nsuccessful prediction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2016 22:35:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-01"}
