tructure of\ninterconnections among participants. This confirms, as recently suggested in\nthe literature, that different coordination levels are achieved over diverse\nvisual pairings in the presence and in the absence of social interaction. We\npresent preliminary experimental results on the effect on group coordination of\ndeploying virtual computer agents in the human ensemble.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 Jul 2016 14:24:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-17"}
